FashionKart 🛒

FashionKart is a full-stack e-commerce platform built using Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and Vanilla JavaScript (Frontend).
It provides users with an interface to browse products, add items to cart, and simulate basic e-commerce functionality.

🚀 Features

User-friendly UI for browsing products.

Backend API with Express and MongoDB.

RESTful routes for handling requests.

Secure connection to MongoDB Atlas.

Deployed on Render for both frontend and backend.

🛠️ Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Backend: Node.js, Express

Database: MongoDB Atlas

Deployment: Render

📦 Installation & Setup
1️⃣ Clone Repository
git clone <your-repo-link>
cd project-folder

2️⃣ Install Dependencies

For backend (server):

cd server
npm install


For frontend (client):

cd client
# (If dependencies exist, install them; else skip)

3️⃣ Environment Variables

Inside server/.env, add:

PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.mongodb.net/mydb
JWT_SECRET=someSecretKey

4️⃣ Run Locally

Backend:

cd server
npm run dev


Open in browser:

http://localhost:5000

🌐 Remote Access

The project is deployed on Render.
👉 Live URL: FashionKart

Database Access

Login to MongoDB Atlas.

Use your Atlas credentials to view collections and documents.

Default Admin Access (if applicable)
Username: admin
Password: admin123


(Change this in production for security.)

📂 Project Structure
project-folder/
│── client/        # Frontend files (HTML, CSS, JS)
│── server/        # Backend (Express + MongoDB)
│   │── src/
│   │   ├── server.js    # Entry point
│   │   ├── config/      # DB config
│   │   ├── routes/      # API routes
│   │   └── models/      # Mongoose schemas
│── README.md     # Documentation
